About this product

Product Information

The Nintendo Game Boy Advance SP features a bright and sharp 2.9 inch backlit and front lit screen. With the ability to display 15 bit color and 512 colors at the same time, every title can come to brilliant life on the 240 x 160 pixel LCD screen. The black graphite clam shell case design can protect both the screen and hardware when the Nintendo Gameboy is in use and when it's not. Thanks to its flip screen design, you can close it for easy portability and storage. With dimensions of 3.1 inches high x 3.23 inches wide x 2.4 inches deep, you can even carry it around in your pocket. This Game Boy Advance weighs only 4.9 ounces by itself and 5.6 ounces with a game cartridge inside, so carrying a world of adventure around with you can be effortless. When opened, the classic button arrangement and D-pad placement are designed especially for user comfort and ease. Those familiar circular A and B buttons sit right where your thumb can comfortably reach them. The adjustable screen boats a flexible range of 185 degrees, so you can easily angle the display to sit exactly where you need and want it. The Nintendo Game Boy Advance SP's easily rechargeable lithium-ion battery can provide 18 hours of play with the light off. On its brighter setting, the battery can stay strong for around 7-10 hours. You can enjoy the many sounds of your Game Boy games with a stereo speaker that sits right among the buttons. When you want to hear your game without it being obvious, you can use your headphones by plugging them into a stereophonic adapter. Simple jacks on the back of the Advance SP can supply a surprising amount of options. Along with an AC adapter, there's a port that can allow you to connect the Advance to the Nintendo GameCube. There's also the Game Boy Game Link jack, which you can use to connect to up to three other players who are using any model Game Boy to battle or play co-op games.
